body:
As far as I can tell this is working as documented.

    // Fields which start and stop with the quote character " are called
    // quoted-fields.  The beginning and ending quote are not part of the
    // field.

    // If LazyQuotes is true, a quote may appear in an unquoted field and a
    // non-doubled quote may appear in a quoted field.

Your field starts with a quote character, and is therefore a _quoted field_.  Setting `LazyQuotes` means that a non-doubled quote may appear in a quoted field, but that is not the case here.

Please feel free to reopen if you disagree.
